Six cards are displayed on a table as follows:
$$\begin{matrix} & \boxed{\tt{A}} & \boxed{\tt{B}} & \boxed{\tt{S}} \\ \boxed{\tt{8}} & \boxed{\tt{5}} & \boxed{\tt{7}} \end{matrix}$$
Each card has a letter on one side and a whole number on the other side. Thomas claims, "If a vowel is on one side of any card, then a prime number is on the other side." Susan attempts to prove Thomas wrong by turning over cards. Which two cards should Susan turn over to potentially disprove Thomas's claim?
- **(A)** { A, 5 }
- **(B)** { A, 7 }
- **(C)** { B, 5 }
- **(D)** { S, 7 }
- **(E)** { B, 8 }
